{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legalise Everyday Carry of Folding Pocket Knives with Common Locking Mechanisms",
        "additional_details": "I believe the addition of a locking mechanism to pocket knives does not increase the risk to public safety; however, it significantly improves user safety by preventing the blade from accidentally folding onto the user's fingers\u2014a frequent cause of injury during normal use.\r\nI believe permitting such mechanisms would substantially reduce injuries caused by folding pocket knives, thereby alleviating unnecessary pressure on NHS A&E departments.",
        "background": "I urge the UK government to include common pocket knife locking mechanisms\u2014such as frame locks, liner locks, back locks, and button locks\u2014under the everyday carry (EDC) exemptions. This change would legalise a wide range of commonly used pocket knives intended for routine, practical tasks.",
